<span style="font-family: pinyon script><font size=8px>Chronicle VI:</font></span><br>
''"The Apothecary"''
----
The fog in the distance made it impossible to see beyond a few meters.

Robert stood fixed to a rickety wooden table, his scalpel prodding into the tough flesh of a Hound specimen. He had labored himself tirelessly for several days in order to find the source of such a blasphemous creature. Working diligently, he carefully inspected the insides of the creature, which had grown purple and discolored from the rot. 

Whilst most Hounds had mutated to adapt to the [[Level 173|endless streams]], this one had chose to stay in the forest, where it and a few others promptly destroyed the [[Backrooms Colonists]] Creek outpost. 

The scalpel sliced open the salivary gland — which contained a sac filled with a sickly green substance, rather than saliva. It was certainly a strange sight, yet he kept inspecting. He scooped out a large portion of the substance from each major gland and poured the substance into a bottle. 

Robert made his way through the endless forest; the river far away and out of sight from his position. He wandered for what he presumed to be days, seeking an exit from the boreal madness — with his legs gradually growing creaky and tired. His experience with medicine proved useful in The Backrooms, as he had been an apothecary [[The Frontrooms|back home]], with his medicines being exceptionally effective.

He passed yet another large boulder, tallying them in his mind as an easy-to-remember landmark. He took a swig out of his bottle...

...

He fell.

...

There was a thud.

...

Robert stirred. "''Am I dead? Have I landed in Satan's chamber?''" He asked himself.

"''No.''" A voice exclaimed. "''You're in the [[Level 4#S.R.C. (Society of the Red Cross: Natural Sciences and Medicine)|S.R.C.]]''"

He inquired: "''Ah, I see. Am I still in a nightmare?''"

The figure sighed. "''Yes, unfortunately. We're all in a nightmare.''" He chuckled, leaning his head against the cold wall.

Robert gasped. "''Where is it? Where is the vial?''"

"''The bottle you came here with? We have it right here. This is- revolutionary. We've never seen anything like it.''"

"''Is this true?''" Robert chimed.

The figure nodded his head. "''We've studied it. Turns out your discovery was a very valuable asset in figuring out the biology of Hounds. Your name is Robert, right?''"

"''Yes, that's true,''" he answered. "''But what day is it again?''"

The figure made a cold gaze at his calendar. "''August, 15, 1993. Why?''"

He looked visibly concerned. "''Nineteen? '''Nineteen''' ninety-three? I could've sworn it had been 1593 just a few odd days prior.''" he uttered.

"''You came from a temporal anomaly, didn't you?''" The figure inquired.

Robert answered: "''I'd assume so, whatever that means.''"

The figure sat down. "''So... anyways, what's your name? I'm curious.''"

"''Robert. Robert Egremond,''" he answered.

The figure responded: "''My name is David, if you were wondering.''"

...


"'''<span style="color: white;">[[Phenomenon_35|David Roth]]</span>.'''"

